This paper presents a novel approach to computational fact checking using knowledge graphs and network flow models. The paper involves natural language processing and machine learning techniques, which are commonly associated with the sub-categories of cs.AI and cs.CL. The use of knowledge graphs and the evaluation on real-world datasets suggest that the paper may also belong to the sub-categories of cs.DB and cs.IR. Finally, the paper's focus on algorithmic performance and optimization may suggest a connection to the sub-category of cs.LG.
